Japanese Sold Net 224 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-07-27T23:55:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/japanese-sold-net-224-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 22 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 224 billion yen ($2.9 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 61.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 37.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 124.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 146 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 2.3 billion yen in stocks, and sold 697.3 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 841
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  